Approach & Future Improvements
My approach focused on designing a playful, kid-friendly landing page using the rounded Nunito font, custom pastel gradients, and bouncy Framer Motion animations to engage parents and children. I structured the frontend with eight modular, responsive components and built an Express.js backend with built-in input validation, CORS support, and an automated MongoDB fallback database connection.

If given more time, I would improve the application by:

Refining responsiveness at landscape tablet breakpoints to ensure pixel-perfect grids.
Migrating the codebase to TypeScript for robust compile-time safety and type definitions.
Implementing server-side schemas using Zod and automated parent email notifications via Nodemailer.
Writing frontend unit tests with Jest and API endpoint integration tests using Supertest.
